channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: New York Times Columnists Rate Kamala Harris As Least Likely to Defeat Trump
Anti-Israel agitators invade Capitol Hill building on eve of Netanyahu address
item.description: Anti-Israel organizers gathered in the Cannon Rotunda on Tuesday afternoon amid Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's visit to D.C.

item.title: Top Zelenskyy Aide Speaks by Phone With Kamala Harris Adviser
item.description: President Volodymyr Zelenskyy's chief of staff spoke by phone with U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris's national security adviser, Ukraine said on Tuesday, the first such call since she emerged as the frontrunner for the Democratic presidential nomination. Andriy Yermak, head...

item.title: Will Joe Biden Leave Office the Same Way He Came In With a Massive US Military Defeat?
Harris' backing of bail fund during George Floyd protests dampens Trump 'prosecutor' campaign pitch
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris is working overtime to prove she has what it takes to not only defeat former President Donald Trump in the 2024 election but also in the courtroom.

item.title: Trump Pollster Warns of Harris 'Honeymoon' in Polls
item.description: Trump campaign pollster Tony Fabrizio is not concerned about recent polls that show Vice President Kamala Harris leading former President Donald Trump, according to a confidential memo obtained by Newsmax.

item.title: Proof of Life? Biden Finally Appears, but Looks Out of It
Trump early strategy targets state that hasn't gone red since Nixon
item.description: Former President Trump and Ohio Sen. JD Vance are taking a trip to St. Cloud, Minnesota for a rally Saturday, hoping to flip a state that has long been dependably blue.

item.title: Sen. Menendez Resigns After Corruption Conviction
item.description: Sen. Bob Menendez, D-N.J., resigned on Tuesday in the aftermath of his conviction on corruption charges including bribery and acting as an agent for Egypt's government, bowing to pressure from fellow Democrats to give up the job. Democrat New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy will ...

item.title: CNN Defamation Suit: Does Unredacted Deposition Show Journo Admitting Their Story Was Wrong?
Trump to meet with Netanyahu at Mar-a-Lago on Friday
item.description: Former President Trump is expected to meet with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu at Mar-a-Lago on Friday.

item.title: Rep. Donalds to Newsmax: Kamala Harris Has Record of Failure
item.description: Rep. Byron Donalds, R-Fla., told Newsmax on Tuesday Vice President Kamala Harris' presidential run will fail because of her poor record.

item.title: CNN's Harry Enten Drops the Reality Hammer on Kamala Harris' Dreams
Bob Menendez to resign from Senate amid Democratic pressure after guilty verdict
item.description: Sen. Bob Menendez, D-N.J., resigned from the Senate after being found guilty in his federal corruption trial and facing near unanimous pressure among his Senate Democratic colleagues to do so.

item.title: Jason Miller to Newsmax: Nobody in Charge of Our Country
item.description: The fact it took so long for Secret Service Director Kimberly Cheatle to resign after her department failed to stop a would-be assassin from wounding former President Donald Trump shows that no one is in charge of the country right now, Jason Miller told Newsmax.
